  "description": "A cross-version core mod for all of my mods.",
  "body": "<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Lieutenant</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"> <strong> <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/mod%20loader-forge-1976d2?style=flat-square\" width=\"112\" height=\"20\" /> <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/environment-both-4caf50?style=flat-square\" width=\"112\" height=\"20\" /> <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/version-1.14,%201.12.2-4caf50?style=flat-square\" width=\"130\" height=\"20\" /> </strong> </span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\">Lieutenant is my general code library, containing redundant code as to reduce the package size of my future mods, and to make distribution of future updates and bug fixes easier.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>May I use this in my own mod?</strong></p>\n<p><em>There is no documentation of this library as of now. However, if you would like to use it, I will not stop you.</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Can I use your mods without this library?</strong></p>\n<p><em>No. My mods will not work without them unless specified otherwise.</em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"> <strong>Can I use this in a modpack? <br /> </strong>Of course! I don't mind. <br /> <br /> <a href=\"https://client.kinetichosting.net/aff.php?aff=38\"> <img src=\"https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1057333762347778240/1057477061465350265/MATTS.png\" /> </a> <br /> </span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://discord.gg/G6HrJk7BBc\"> <img src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/logopedia/images/0/05/Discord.svg\" width=\"144\" height=\"39\" /> </a></p>",
